## Per-slide self-check (run on each assertion row before declaring it done)

- [ ] Title is a complete sentence stating a conclusion (not a topic).
- [ ] One assertion per slide (no "and" joining two claims).
- [ ] Visual is specified well enough the user can tell whether an existing figure fits or a new one is needed.
- [ ] Every axis/label/panel on the visual has a sentence the speaker will say about it — otherwise cut or build progressively.
- [ ] Transitions in and out are single sentences.
- [ ] Speaker notes contain at least one of: specific number, skeptic pre-empt, pacing cue.
- [ ] The assertion is a step in the Storyline arc — traceable back to a dive or beat.
